AGI -&nbsp; Yesterday the workers of the Remediation Consortium of Central Sardinia put the seals to the water meter of a breeder, after having surprised him to irrigate his medical field in the campaigns of Siniscola (Nuoro), in violation of the prohibition imposed 15 days ago by an order of the mayor. In this part of Nuorese, Baronia, the water crisis hits hard, breeders and farmers are at despair. So this morning around 11:30 pm one of them, Giovanni Bomboi, 42 years old, municipal councilman of Siniscola, presented himself armed with gun in the offices of the Consortium on the outskirts of the town on the eastern coast of Sardinia. Shortly before he had called, with threatening tone, to ask that the supply of water be restored, indispensable for drinking livestock, but he had been explained that he should contact Nuoro's offices. Instead, the lifter, in a strong state of agitation, showed up in front of the gate of the seat of Siniscola, demanding the immediate restoration of access to water. The workers, from the courtyard, reiterated that they could do nothing for him. At that point, the man shot at man's height, 6-7 hits, without hitting anyone, fortunately. The bullets were stuck in a wall, in a door and a middle of the consortium. Then the climber escaped, being unavailable until 18.30 when he showed up in the offices of the Mobile Team, with the mediation of his lawyer, Francesco Carboni. You'll have to answer the investigator's questions, you're risking attempted murder.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The violation of the order also provides for a penalty of one hundred euros. "I don't understand why he had this reaction," says AGI&nbsp; Ambrogio Guiso, president of the Remediation Consortium. "We know that the situation is of total emergency, because in Baronia it has not rained for months and the regional cabin has had to decide the total closure of irrigation in the full field, and also of meadows and gardens. But, as a Consortium, we try to meet farmers and farmers and we would have done so in this case. The point is that in the Maccheronis dam, which serves the irrigation district, there are just 8 million cubic meters of water, 30% of the capacity. With estimated consumption of 50 thousand cubic metres per day, we reach the maximum until early August." So the restrictions were inevitable. The five municipalities of the irriguous district of Posada - Siniscola, Budoni, San Teodoro, Torpe' and Posada - have, one after the other, decreed the state of natural magnetism and arranged the prohibition of use of water for irrigation purposes and to water meadows and gardens. Except for livestock and domestic uses. The controls were entrusted to urban traffic, barracks, workers of the Consortium and staff of the Regional Forestry Corps. And yesterday Bomboi, who must feed and drink to his cattle and sheep, was surprised by employees of the Consortium of reclamation to violate the prohibition.
&nbsp;
"We are aware of the great discomfort that farms are experiencing served by the irrigated infrastructure of the district of Posada, which unfortunately must comply with the prohibition of irrigation, but it's a situation that we can not manage in any other way - says Guiso -. For this reason we invite everyone to calm and active collaboration. Unfortunately, the grave drought does not put other solutions than that of restrictions. We don't get into the merits of what happened," he adds.
&nbsp;
"We are certainly very bitter. But we believe that the lack of water resources is a problem that must be dealt with immediately by giving answers to the territory. We must take action with extraordinary measures and support the agricultural sector. Weeks ago I made it present to the prefect of Nuoro: The situation in Siniscola is becoming explosive. The people of the countryside are suffering, they don't know how to feed the beasts, since there is no chance to have grass from the fields," he reminds AGI&nbsp; the mayor Gian Luigi Farris, who had to sign the order with the restrictions. "So breeders are forced to spend on feed and forage, resulting in this way animals drink more than when fed with fresh grass. I'm very sorry for what happened. I know Bomboi and she's a good person." The municipal councilman, elected on the mayor's list, was then passed into the minority bank. "It must have been a wrath attack," adds the first citizen. "Let's hope he doesn't do anything. The mayor's worried about the tourist season. "What's going to happen in the next few months when 100,000 people arrive?" Today, a few drops of rain fell into Baronia, but it should rain for days to restore stocks in the Maccheronis invader. "Siniscola always shared the water with everyone when it was necessary. This time we need it; I hope they help us and bring the water from the invaded Liscia. If tourism is missing - paventa Farris - it will take years to this territory to recover". &nbsp;

