AGI - The Prosecutor of Grosseto has placed the arrest with the charge of murder for a woman with Filipino nationality accused of killing her newborn son born on a cruise ship about two days before. The 28-year-old woman, according to what she learned, is part of the crew, where she is a cleaning officer and in all these months she would have kept her pregnancy hidden.
&nbsp;
As much as learned, the woman after childbirth would only leave the child in her cabin, where he was found dead. It was the colleagues who gave the alarm on Sunday evening when the ship, flying the Bamahas flag, arrived in Porto Santo Stefano.
&nbsp;
The Carabinieri intervened on board for the reliefs of the case. The 28-year-old Filipino was taken to the hospital for health inspections. Prosecutor cleared autopsy on the baby.

