AGI - "Hello everyone. I wanted to make sure I'm okay. I had a problem this weekend but nothing serious. I don't know why they're saying I'm in the end of my life." Fedez writes on his Instagram page after the rumors, then denied, that he had been admitted for an aggravation of his illness.
&nbsp;
The rapper couldn't record the episode of Cattelan's program that will be aired tonight.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"We all know that Federico's attention is always very high. When we called him a long time ago, we initially had thought of a nice thing, I wanted to be a surprise guest at a wedding, which was fun seeing what is happening with his... I'm joking because he always lent himself with me. Subsequently, given recent events, we had considered a different treatment. Now Federico has told us that he will not be able to be there for health reasons, I can only wish him luck because he gets back to the best," he said to Corriere della Sera Alessandro Cattelan, conductor of "Next is normal", three first evening show on Rai 2 from tonight, about the lack of participation of Fedez.&nbsp;

