"I can boast of being the most honest person I know. I never stole a lira and if I fell into something really incorrect, I'm ready to pay." He has the bitter and disturbed voice, it is said "unpacked", speaking with&nbsp;AGI, the former president of the Sicilian Regional Assembly, Gianfranco&nbsp;Micciche, former leader of FI in Sicily, after the investigation at his expense of the prosecutor of Palermo. The politician and his driver are challenged, for various reasons, the criminal offences, a fraud aggravated by the damages of the Sicilian Regional Assembly and false statements on the presence in service of a public employee. For this reason the gip of Palermo, accepting the requests of the prosecutor led by Maurizio de Lucia, issued the prohibition of residence in the commune of Cefalu' for Micciche', as well as the obligation of residence in the Municipalities of Palermo and Monreale towards Maurizio Messina, parliamentary assistant with functions of driver of&nbsp;Micciche'.
